    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="984"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d984">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14115.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>It is certain that if a convention meets here tomorrow it will contain most
                    antagonistic elements. The Zapata element will endeavor <pb facs="0752" n="636"
                        xml:id="pg_636"/> to dominate. They expect to have the support of Villa. The
                    friends of the Provisional President expect him to develop more strength than
                    his enemies give him credit for. His enemies are quite confident of his complete
                    downfall. There is an unconfirmed rumor that Villa will proclaim himself
                    dictator. He has personally assumed the censorship of the federal telegraph in
                    this city.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
